## M20i.1.1 (post-impl review): capturing the loop-borrow element in
## an inner lambda is rejected.
##
## Per GPT-5.5's M20i.1 post-impl review (conversation entry 28):
## the loop element binding `cb` is a borrowed view of the Vec slot
## (`?*Closure()` in sema's type vocabulary). The clone-capture
## mode `|+cb|` requires a `shared (*T)` or `weak (~T)` operand;
## a borrow does not qualify. M20g's existing clone-capture
## validator fires the appropriate diagnostic — defense-in-depth
## alongside the M20i.1 `rejectLoopBorrowOp` machinery.
##
## Without this rejection, capturing the loop-borrow into an
## escaping closure (`f: *Closure() = *Closure(|+cb| cb())`)
## would smuggle the borrowed handle past the loop boundary,
## defeating the entire purpose of binding the element as a
## borrowed view.

sub main()
  count: *Cell(Int) = *Cell(value: 0)
  cb1: *Closure() = *Closure(|+count| count.set(count.get() + 1))

  subs: Vec(*Closure()) = Vec()
  (!subs).push(+cb1)

  for cb in ?subs
    f = |+cb| cb()
    f()
